cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

Reasoning: The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as semantic segmentation, human parts segmentation, and saliency estimation, which are typically covered under the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also introduces a new subnetwork of a deep architecture and trains it end-to-end with backpropagation, which falls under the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The use of low-rank linear systems and conjugate gradients for efficient minimization of energy is related to optimization techniques covered under the cs.NE sub-category. Finally, the use of the Caffe library and GPU-based implementation is related to the cs.MM sub-category.
